 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .\n7\n\nAssumptions and Constraints\n8\n7\nFuture Scope\n8\n8\nConclusion\n8\n2\n\n1 Introduction\n1.1 \tProject Background\nAgriculture and livestock farming in many regions still rely on manual record keeping. Farmers maintain registers for animal health, breeding cycles, milk production, employee duties, and sales. This traditional system often leads to data loss, incorrect decision making, and financial inefficiency.\nThe AgriPrime system is proposed as a unified digital platform that manages livestock lifecycle, workforce operations, veterinary health, inventory, logistics, and an online e-commerce marketplace.\n1.2 \tPurpose of Document\nThis document describes the functional and non-functional requirements gathered from the client after multiple meetings and requirement elicitation sessions.\n1.3 \tScope\nThe system will:\n\u2022 Track livestock from birth/purchase to sale\n\u2022 Manage veterinary health and vaccination\n\u2022 Handle employee management and payroll\n\u2022 Provide online selling platform\n\u2022 Maintain financial analytics and reporting\n2 Client Meeting Case Scenario\n2.1 \tInitial Contact\nThe client, Mr. Ahmed (Farm Owner), operates a medium-scale livestock farm supplying dairy products and live animals. The meeting took place at the farm office where current manual registers were observed.\n3\n\n2.2 \tClient Problems Observed\n\u2022 Animal records stored in notebooks\n\u2022 Difficulty tracking vaccination schedules\n\u2022 Employees forgetting assigned duties\n\u2022 Animals sometimes sold twice due to poor tracking\u2022 No online selling platform\n2.3 \tClient Expectations \nThe client requested:\n\u2022 A centralized digital system\n\u2022 Automatic reminders for animal health\u2022 Easy employee monitoring\n\u2022 Online marketplace integration\n\u2022 Profit tracking per animal\n3 Stakeholders\n\u2022 Farm Owner (Primary decision maker)\n\u2022 Veterinarian\n\u2022 Farm Workers\n\u2022 Accountant\n\u2022 Customers\n\u2022 Delivery Staff\n4\n\n4 Functional Requirements\n4.1 \tLivestock Management Module \nClient Requirement: The client wanted every animal to have a digital identity.\nSystem Solution:\n\u2022 Unique RFID/Tag ID\n\u2022 Breed and lineage tracking\n\u2022 Weight history storage\n\u2022 Lifecycle status monitoring\nUser Story: As a Farm Manager, I want to search any animal instantly so that I can view its history.\n4.2 \tBreeding Management \nClient emphasized genetic quality improvement.\nSystem provides:\n\u2022 Heat cycle alerts\n\u2022 Pregnancy tracking\n\u2022 Offspring auto-registration\nUser Story: As a veterinarian, I want breeding alerts so that reproduction success increases.\n4.3 \tVeterinary Module \nClient Issue: Vaccinations were often missed.\nSolution:\n\u2022 Automated vaccination reminders\n\u2022 Treatment logs\n\u2022 Quarantine tagging\nUser Story: As a vet, I want medical history instantly accessible.\n5\n\n4.4 \tInventory and Feed Management Client needed feed cost control.\nSystem Features:\n\u2022 Feed stock monitoring\n\u2022 Diet planning for animal groups\n\u2022 Medicine expiry alerts\n4.5 \tHR Management \nClient wanted accountability among workers.\nSystem Provides:\n\u2022 Employee profiles\n\u2022 Attendance tracking\n\u2022 Task assignment\n\u2022 Payroll automation\nUser Story: As an owner, I want to know which worker completed which task.\n4.6 \tE-Commerce Module \nClient Goal: Expand business beyond physical buyers.\nFeatures:\n\u2022 Online animal listings\n\u2022 Product marketplace\n\u2022 Secure checkout\n\u2022 Customer dashboard\n4.7 \tOrder Management System\u2022 Order lifecycle tracking\n\u2022 Inventory locking\n\u2022 Status updates\n6\n\n4.8 \tLogistics Module\nClient Concern: Animal delivery safety.\nSolution:\n\u2022 Vehicle tracking\n\u2022 Route assignment\n\u2022 Digital gate pass\n4.9 \tFinancial Module\nClient wanted profit visibility.\nSystem calculates:\n\u2022 Expenses\n\u2022 Revenue\n\u2022 Profit per animal\n5 Non Functional Requirements\n5.1 \tPerformance\nSystem must handle large animal records efficiently.\n5.2 \tSecurity\n\u2022 Role Based Access Control\n\u2022 JWT Authentication\n\u2022 Secure payment processing\n5.3 \tUsability\nInterface must be simple for non-technical farm staff.\n5.4 \tScalability\nSystem should support expansion to multiple farms.\n7\n\n6 Assumptions and Constraints\n\u2022 Internet connectivity available at farm office\u2022 Users have basic smartphone knowledge\u2022 MongoDB used for flexible schema storage\n7 Future Scope\n\u2022 AI disease detection using images\n\u2022 Smart IoT weight sensors\n\u2022 Automated milk yield prediction\n8 Conclusion\nThe AgriPrime system transforms traditional livestock management into a smart digital ecosystem. The requirements gathered directly reflect real operational challenges faced by the client and aim to improve efficiency, profitability, and scalability.\n8": null}